social_posts.post_text: Highlights from a WILD week of filming @sistersummit_ ! First time going on a shoot and not taking a single photo 🙀

Many moments with my camera to be grateful for in 2022 but these were some of the tippy top times. 

01 -  @sophie_danison filming for @nxusfilm  in Revy. Dream. Shit fuck conditions -- but the crew made magic anyways. Watch the movie to find out how. I mean, look at these foggy-ass trees!

02 - @vasu_sojitra closing @yogikira ‘s 8s on a gorgeous afternoon in the Tetons for @subaru_usa. Was a joy to finally get to meet and work with this crew after hearing so much about them over the years. 

03 - @sophie_danison and @morgankelsey at Great Divide. We went on a 10 day road trip for MT Tourism at five small rural ski areas, shooting photos and engaging in many shenanigans. There’s still nothing like that small-ski-area-single-chairlift-vibe. 

05 - @bendh and I spotted this panel and couldn’t help ourselves.  A memorable winter of personal skiing in Cooke City. 

06- The first expedition of three for @griffpost & Teton Gravity’s Chasing Washburn project. We were supposed to be looking for a lost camera, but kept getting distracted…

06 - @gretchen_gerlach convinces me that canoeing is fun. 

07 - @yawahawolowo spreads knowledge at her farm in Cuba, Alabama. This was one of two summer projects for @patagonia_workwear documenting @wwoofusa documenting wwoof hosts and future farmers. 

08 - Bradford Washburn’s camera, left behind in 1937, found by a curious crew of freeriders, cameramen, and glaciologists turned treasure hunters. 

09 -  @rivianofficial at the Rebelle Rally - an all-women navigational rally that spans Nevada to Cali over 8 days. A real challenge and treat to be there. 

10 - and finally, @leilani.rose.b convinces me that bike packing is fun.
2023 mood board.
Seems like our little corner of the rocky mountain west is the only dry place left this “winter.” Trying not to go crazy over here, waiting for the good stuff.
From the drafts, the reel Montana tourism didn’t know they asked for. Missing these gals big time and the many carpets of the maverick mountain lodge.
A never ending winter. ❄️❄️❄️

Patagonia Sportswear, Spring 2022, Alaska. Part 1/3

Last June my dear friend Gretchen invited me to join her and her colleagues on a weeklong ocean canoeing expedition launching from Wrangell, AK. 
All of them guides - I was along for the ride, doing something I never ever thought I’d do. Thanks to this crew for showing me your world, catching dinner, and keeping ‘er straight while I took an absurd amount of breaks from the ores to snap pics!

Bikepacking the Baja Cope Loop - November 2022. PT. 1/3

Bikepacking the Baja Cope Loop -  2022. PT. 2/3

I fell in love with bikes in 2019 (ish?!) when @sophie_danison went on the river and left her trusty Cannondale in my hands. Since then I just can't stay away. I want to do all the bike things in all the forms... ok except maybe road biking... 

This trip to Baja with this crew was one I will never forget. Pedaling through the rural center of a place most people only see the edges of (it's full of puppies, farmers and hill climbs). Getting from checkpoint to checkpoint, rewards of tacos, cold cervesas, or epic beach camp keeping us motivated. A relatively soft entry to the world of bike packing—perfect for fooling us into planning the next trip.
Bikepacking the Baja Cope Loop - November 2022. PT. 3/3... Thanks for listening...

@lily.krass.ritter wrote a very kind story about my growth as a photographer and filmmaker in the ski and snowboard world in @theskijournal and I honestly don’t really know how to thank her for it. A lot of us photogs have been working at this dream for years and years (in high school I had an entire wall in my room dedicated to tear-out pages of photos from Powder) and getting featured like this in a magazine like The Ski Journal is an absolute dream come true. And I really feel that. Thank you to Lily and @kadekrichko and @andrew_marshall - appreciate you guys and what you do ❤️. 

Here are some of the shots from the feature! I wrote some detailed captions about the story behind these frames and you can read them in the mag. :)

Double duty for @rivianofficial last week filming and photographing three Rivians crossing the finish line of the @rebellerally ! Extra special because @lillymacamazing and @alexandra_m_anderson won- making history as the first team to win the race in an all electric vehicle. ⚡️⚡️⚡️ Extra extra special for me because I filmed Lily and Alex’s go at it last year and got to see first hand just how much skill it takes to do one of these things, let alone win the damn thing. ❤️congratulations to all and thank you for having me along.

This silly shot of @bendh dealing with the aftermath of a leaky dry bag on the Grand Canyon is a @redbullillume semi finalist in the lifestyle category! Fun to make it in and grateful to Ben for being fine with me just taking photos and not helping… 🩷😬
